is "semiotics," "death of the author" and "enunciation theory".

00:31:35.160 --> 00:31:37.760
Most of what I've said doesn't only apply to stories,

00:31:37.760 --> 00:31:39.540
but to any creative work that needs interpreting.

00:31:39.540 --> 00:31:43.240
My discussion of critical theory is not at all comprehensive,

00:31:43.520 --> 00:31:47.680
and maybe not all academics would agree with the way I'm mushing these schools of thought together,

00:31:47.720 --> 00:31:52.440
